-- Fog Idles 10 Houston-Bound Ships, U.S. Coast Guard Reports
-- B y   J i m   P o l s o n
-- 2013-03-18T11:22:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-18/fog-idles-10-houston-bound-ships-u-s-coast-guard-reports.html
Fog has idled 10 ships bound for
Houston, the largest U.S. petroleum port, the U.S. Coast Guard
reported.  Another 12 ships are waiting to depart, Lieutenant David
Vihonski, a Coast Guard watch supervisor, said today in a
telephone interview. Pilots suspended boardings at 11:15 p.m.
local time yesterday because of reduced visibility from dense
fog, the Coast Guard said.  A dense fog advisory is in effect until 9 a.m. local time
today, according to the  National Weather Service .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jim Polson in  New York  at 
 jpolson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
